- Tue 14 Aug 2018. Ebola virus disease - Democratic Republic of Congo, WHO/AFRO external situation report 02
[WHO AFRO Outbreaks <afrooutbreak@who.int>, edited]
http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/handle/10665/273867/SITREP_EVD_DRC_20180814-eng.pdf

The Ministry of Health in the Democratic Republic of the Congo, WHO, and partners are responding to a new Ebola virus disease (EVD) outbreak in the eastern North Kivu province. ...[more]

As of 11 Aug 2018, a total of 990 contacts are under surveillance in Mabalako (790), Beni (141), and Mandima (59) health zones. Of these, 129 are healthcare workers in Mabalako (72) and Beni (57) health zones. On 11 Aug 2018, 940 (95 percent) contacts were successfully followed up.

